File: Afriforum. JOHANNESBURG - A centralised power supply system has failed South Africa, so why not try decentralising? That's the rationale behind AfriForum's plans for a new power company. AfriForum CEO Kallie Kriel says there should be multiple providers of electricity that focus on specific regions. Kriel says it's a system that's already working in one area. He was speaking to Prof JJ Tabane on Power To Truth. Watch the full episode here.